<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <xar:if condition="file_exists('modules/chat/xarimages/pjirclogo.gif')" >
                <img src="modules/chat/xarimages/pjirclogo.gif" alt="official icon" width="131" height="102" />
            <xar:else />
                <img src="modules/modules/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="131" height="102" />
            </xar:if></div>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <em><xar:mlstring>The Chat Module is a content module</xar:mlstring></em>
            <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing these tasks:</xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Allowing a user to attach to an IRC server via their browser.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Chat module is based on PJIRC, an opensource chat client.  All source and credits are included in this distribution under the xarjava directory.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>Configure the server, port (6667 is standard) and channel that you want to open when the chat is launched.</xar:mlstring>

        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>There are no included hooks.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
